        to its ground state with emission of one or more &#947; photons, without any change of A or Z. 
        For example when Co-60 decays to an excited state of Ni-60 
        by &#946; decay, two gammas of energies 1.173 MeV and 1.332 MeV are rapidly emitted.
        <br/><br/>
        &#947; rays are highly <strong>penetrating</strong> making them useful 
        medically, but also hazardous. Effective shielding requires a large 
        amount of mass, such as thick concrete walls. The main <strong>interaction 
        processes</strong> with matter (resulting in ionization and dose) are the
         photoelectric effect, Compton scattering, and electron-positron pair production. 

